subject: Install service unit files, busconfig and udev rules from the package.

SG

I think you should use pkgconfig to find 'udev.pc' and get the udev_dir out of it.  If you can't find that, then I think you can default to:

get_option('prefix') / 'lib/udev/rules.d'

The bitbake SDK has udev.pc which has the right information in it.

The pkgconfig lookup should be very similar to how 'systemd_system_unit_dir' is obtained.

The pkgconfig file contains only libdir for the actual libraries.
The "prefix" option is unsuitable for sure (it prepends /usr).

The systemd/meson defines paths as follows:

> udevlibexecdir = join_paths(rootprefixdir, 'lib/udev')
> udevrulesdir = join_paths(udevlibexecdir, 'rules.d')

The "libdir" prefix is also wrong, because it will provide a machine-dependent path (e.g. /lib or /lib64), while the rules dir stays the same all the time: /usr/udev/rules.d regardless the arch bitness.

I'm going to pass "udevrulesdir" option.
Can you reuse this from parent directory?
